# Slot Machine

A command-line slot machine game with emoji symbols, betting, and a payout system.

## Description

This program simulates a slot machine with a starting balance of $100. The player places a bet each round, spins three random emoji symbols, and wins a payout if all three match. Each symbol has its own multiplier, with rarer symbols paying out more. The game continues until the player runs out of money or decides to quit.

## Concepts Covered

- Functions
- List comprehensions
- The `random` module
- Loops (`while`)
- Conditionals (`if`, `elif`, `else`)
- Input validation
- F-strings
- String methods (`.isdigit()`, `.upper()`)

## Goals

- Practice using list comprehensions to generate random results
- Build a payout system using conditionals and multipliers
- Handle and validate multiple types of user input
- Manage a running balance across multiple rounds
- Create a fun, complete game with a clear win/lose condition
